Hi Cartesia team,

We're an EU-based B2B SaaS (Mindrails UG, Berlin, Germany) building
phonbot.de — a voice-agent platform that uses Cartesia for text-to-
speech in production. Cartesia is in our published sub-processor list
at https://phonbot.de/sub-processors/.

Under GDPR Article 28, we need a signed Data Processing Agreement in
place before going live. Could you please send:

1. Your standard Data Processing Addendum (DPA) — pre-signed PDF or
   DocuSign link.

2. EU Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC) — Module 3 (processor-to-
   processor) appended to the DPA.

3. Confirmation of your current DPF (EU-US Data Privacy Framework)
   certification status, if any.

4. Confirmation that text input sent via your API is NOT used for
   model training (zero-retention commitment for API tier).

5. A list of any sub-processors Cartesia in turn relies on (hosting,
   GPU compute, etc.) and their country of operation.

If you don't currently maintain a standard DPA template, we can share
ours as a starting point — just let us know.

